item.title: Error Help PLease?
item.dc:creator: @kupo kupo
item.description:
@kupo wrote:

You deleted the void packetprocess() I can see if I have it quick[br][size=1]Posted on: May 29, 2007, 04:05:46 PM[/size][hr][code] private boolean packetProcess() {
if(disconnected) return false;
try {
if(timeOutCounter++ > 20) {
actionReset();
disconnected = true;
return false; }

		if(in == null) return false;

		int avail = in.available();
		if(avail == 0) return false;
		if(packetType == -1) {
			packetType = in.read() & 0xff;
			if(inStreamDecryption != null)
				packetType = packetType - inStreamDecryption.getNextKey() & 0xff;
			packetSize = packetSizes[packetType];
			avail--;  }
		if(packetSize == -1) {
			if(avail > 0) {
				packetSize = in.read() & 0xff;
				avail--; }
			else return false; }
		if(avail < packetSize) return false;
		fillInStream(packetSize);
        timeOutCounter = 0;

		parseIncomingPackets();	
		packetType = -1;
	} catch(java.lang.Exception __ex) {	__ex.printStackTrace();  disconnected = true;
              System.out.println("FinalScape Server [fatal] - exception"); }
	return true;
}[/code]

It’s a boolean… close enough
